The paper deals with multi-document summarization, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). The privacy-preserving aspect of the approach suggests that it may also be relevant to computer security (cs.CR). The use of hashing and bit strings suggests that the paper may also be relevant to data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). Finally, the evaluation of the system's performance suggests that it may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG).
